This category of Mitigations describes various measures aimed at providing mental health support and resources to individuals. These measures include promoting access to mental health services, increasing social support networks, providing counseling services, offering financial assistance programs, and creating online content for psychological support. The goal is to enhance access to mental health care, promote self-care practices, and ensure individuals have the resources and support needed to address their mental health needs. Additionally, there is an emphasis on promoting healthy coping mechanisms, addressing economic challenges, and combating discrimination. The Mitigations also involve implementing strategies to monitor mental health and stress reactions, screening for mental health problems, and promoting understanding and empathy. There is a focus on providing accurate information, promoting mental health awareness, and offering virtual options for social activities. Overall, these Mitigations aim to strengthen psychosocial support, address mental health concerns, and promote well-being and resilience.